HEADWORD: Microphyte
<hw>Mi"cro*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a plant: cf. F.
<ets>microphyte</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A very minute
plant, one of certain unicellular algae, such as the germs of various
infectious diseases are believed to be.</def>⟦br⟧
